WEBVTT

00:10.594 --> 00:12.012
♪ You could do it solo ♪

00:12.012 --> 00:13.972
♪ But then you'd be all by yourself ♪

00:13.972 --> 00:15.432
♪ Yo! So, it'd be more fun ♪

00:15.432 --> 00:17.976
♪ To share this one with someone else ♪

00:17.976 --> 00:21.730
♪ Together we will soar
Across the sky and beyond ♪

00:21.730 --> 00:23.106
♪ So turn up your voice ♪

00:23.857 --> 00:25.734
♪ Stand up and sing along ♪

00:25.734 --> 00:26.985
♪ All different voices ♪

00:26.985 --> 00:27.903
♪ Everybody now! ♪

00:27.903 --> 00:29.488
♪ Our melodies ringing ♪

00:29.488 --> 00:31.114
♪ We're livin' in harmony ♪

00:31.114 --> 00:33.242
♪ Yeah, we're livin' In harmony ♪

00:33.242 --> 00:35.244
♪ Our song is much stronger ♪

00:35.244 --> 00:37.037
♪ With every Troll singing ♪

00:37.037 --> 00:39.456
♪ We're livin' in harmony ♪♪

00:43.752 --> 00:47.339
[ cheering ]

00:47.339 --> 00:49.675
‐ Cannonball!

00:50.175 --> 00:51.093
Ah!

00:52.010 --> 00:53.679
Oh, gotta take care of the bunker.

00:54.513 --> 00:55.722
‐ Ow...
‐ Ow...

00:56.598 --> 00:59.768
‐ Woo‐ho‐ho! Oh‐ho‐ho! Yeah!

00:59.768 --> 01:03.855
‐ Woo‐hoo, ya'll!
He'll set the new record in 3, 2...!

01:04.398 --> 01:06.108
‐ Oh, gotta take care of the bunker!

01:07.067 --> 01:08.235
ALL:
Ow...

01:08.610 --> 01:11.363
‐ Who's ready for a stage dive?

01:11.363 --> 01:12.990
[ cheering ]

01:12.990 --> 01:14.700
‐ Over here! Over here, Val!

01:14.700 --> 01:16.493
‐ Huh? Oh! Bunker!

01:17.452 --> 01:18.287
VAL:
Oh!

01:18.287 --> 01:19.329
ALL:
Ow...

01:19.538 --> 01:20.497
[ Val grunts ]

01:22.749 --> 01:23.709
‐ Branch!
‐ Branch!

01:24.293 --> 01:25.127
‐ Hello...

01:25.460 --> 01:27.754
four people speaking in unison.

01:27.963 --> 01:30.716
‐ For the sweet love of hugs, Branch!

01:30.716 --> 01:34.636
You have been cutting short fun
to go work on your bunker for weeks!

01:35.137 --> 01:38.807
‐ Ugh, I know.
Maintaining my bunker and being a Troll

01:38.807 --> 01:40.726
has always been tricky to juggle,

01:40.726 --> 01:44.104
but with all the new tribes
it's way harder.

01:44.104 --> 01:46.356
I mean, I've gotten
three party invitations

01:46.356 --> 01:48.191
just while I've been standing here!

01:48.191 --> 01:49.860
TROLL:
Make that four, partner!

01:51.611 --> 01:52.988
All right, friendship.

01:53.864 --> 01:54.698
‐ See?

01:54.698 --> 01:56.408
‐ Well, hey, if you need a hand,

01:56.408 --> 01:58.201
you can always ask one of us for help!

01:58.618 --> 02:00.871
‐ Let someone else
take care of the bunker?

02:01.330 --> 02:02.164
I don't know...

02:02.372 --> 02:03.623
POPPY:
Please, Branch.

02:03.623 --> 02:06.501
I mean, we all know
how strong your feelings are

02:06.501 --> 02:09.338
for that bunker,
so I get that you're a little scared

02:09.338 --> 02:11.465
to trust it to someone else's care, but‐‐

02:11.465 --> 02:12.341
BRANCH:
What?

02:13.592 --> 02:15.677
I'm not scared, Poppy.

02:15.677 --> 02:18.055
The bunker is just
very difficult to maintain,

02:18.055 --> 02:20.390
and I don't know
how I'd find a Troll who could‐‐

02:21.099 --> 02:22.142
Oh, that's it!

02:22.684 --> 02:25.187
Meet me at my bunker tomorrow.
No time for clarity!

02:27.022 --> 02:29.107
‐ I wonder what Branch
is up to this time...

02:30.108 --> 02:31.652
BRANCH:
Welcome, candidates!

02:32.861 --> 02:34.071
Over the next few hours,

02:34.071 --> 02:36.657
you will be participating
in a series of tests

02:36.657 --> 02:38.867
to assess your fitness as the official...

02:39.242 --> 02:40.118
Bunker Nanny.

02:41.745 --> 02:42.996
‐ "Bunker Nanny?"

02:43.413 --> 02:46.875
Goodness, Branch, don'tcha ever
get tired of bein' so dang cute?

02:47.042 --> 02:50.128
‐ Yeah, save some adorable
for the rest of us, yo.

02:50.671 --> 02:53.757
‐ Now, bunker life can be a lot of fun.

02:53.757 --> 02:57.052
It's quiet, there's dirt,
but none of that can happen

02:57.052 --> 02:58.970
without proper bunker maintenance.

02:59.137 --> 03:00.972
Like underground reinforcement...

03:07.562 --> 03:09.314
‐ Oh!
‐ Oh!

03:09.314 --> 03:10.482
‐ Tunnel tidying...

03:14.736 --> 03:16.196
‐ Ah!
‐ Ah!

03:16.947 --> 03:19.032
‐ And I can't stress
how important this is.

03:19.199 --> 03:22.577
Every 6 hours and 23 minutes you must...

03:23.370 --> 03:24.538
jiggle the handle.

03:24.996 --> 03:27.249
‐ Why? What happens
if you don't jiggle the‐‐?

03:27.249 --> 03:28.083
‐ Shh!

03:28.083 --> 03:34.047
[ groaning ]

03:39.094 --> 03:41.972
‐ Okay! Over here
you'll notice the sweat jars

03:41.972 --> 03:44.641
are arranged alpha‐sweatically...

03:44.641 --> 03:45.475
[ giggle ]

03:45.600 --> 03:46.435
Fun.

03:47.727 --> 03:50.230
Bunker Nanny test number one: Security.

03:50.439 --> 03:53.233
The primary function of a bunker
is to keep things out‐‐

03:53.358 --> 03:54.693
Don't even think about it!

03:54.693 --> 03:57.529
[ alarm ringing ]

03:57.904 --> 04:01.324
So! Let's test to see
whom you decide to let in.

04:01.867 --> 04:02.701
Biggie!

04:02.701 --> 04:03.702
[ cheering ]

04:03.702 --> 04:05.579
HOLLY:
Biggie, you got this!

04:06.496 --> 04:08.540
[ laugh ]

04:11.001 --> 04:14.796
‐ Biggie! Why did you let that Troll in?
He's dressed like a robber!

04:14.796 --> 04:18.341
‐ Well, I assumed he was
attending the big costume party.

04:18.341 --> 04:20.135
‐ Who said there was a costume party?

04:20.552 --> 04:21.511
[ laugh ]

04:21.511 --> 04:23.096
‐ Branch, we're Trolls...

04:24.055 --> 04:26.725
there's always a costume party.

04:26.725 --> 04:27.768
‐ Yeah!
‐ Yeah!

04:27.976 --> 04:29.019
‐ Ugh.

04:29.227 --> 04:30.687
Someone else please go.

04:31.688 --> 04:33.648
[ growl ]

04:36.276 --> 04:39.196
‐ Synth! You just let
a growl beast into my bunker!

04:39.529 --> 04:40.989
‐ Correction, bro!

04:40.989 --> 04:44.785
I let a Troll dressed like a growl beast
into the costume party!

04:45.243 --> 04:46.787
‐ Grr, there is no‐‐! Just‐‐

04:47.370 --> 04:48.330
Poppy, you go!

04:49.164 --> 04:49.998
‐ Hello!

04:50.665 --> 04:51.958
[ alarm ringing ]

04:51.958 --> 04:53.752
‐ Wha‐‐? Poppy, that's me!

04:53.752 --> 04:55.754
‐ Yeah, and you're not wearing a costume.

04:56.588 --> 04:58.006
‐ Yeah, I agree.
‐ Yeah.

04:58.006 --> 04:58.882
‐ Gah!

05:00.175 --> 05:01.843
Bunker Nanny test number two:

05:03.595 --> 05:04.888
Isolation Chamber.

05:06.056 --> 05:07.557
Let's see how well you handle

05:07.557 --> 05:10.268
long stretches of time alone
down here in the bunker...

05:10.769 --> 05:14.272
‐ Pfft! This'll be a piece of cupca‐‐!

05:14.272 --> 05:15.273
[ scream ]

05:15.273 --> 05:18.485
‐ No, I can't! I missed you all too much!

05:18.485 --> 05:19.986
‐ It's okay.
‐ Baby...

05:19.986 --> 05:21.071
[ Branch grunts ]

05:24.699 --> 05:25.951
[ gasp ]

05:26.409 --> 05:29.663
‐ That's it! I gave it everything I had!

05:30.163 --> 05:31.206
Time!

05:32.040 --> 05:33.250
‐ Seven seconds.

05:33.917 --> 05:34.960
‐ Well, hot dang!

05:34.960 --> 05:37.420
[ cheering ]

05:37.963 --> 05:39.256
[ Branch grunts ]

05:39.256 --> 05:42.050
‐ Wow! Poppy's been in there
over three hours.

05:42.050 --> 05:45.136
I mean,
I'm not impressed easily, but this is‐‐

05:45.136 --> 05:48.515
‐ Woo! Isolation party!

05:48.515 --> 05:50.141
[ cheering ]

05:50.141 --> 05:52.686
‐ Poppy‐‐? How did you even‐‐?

05:52.686 --> 05:57.065
‐ Oh, you're just in time!
We're about to cut the isolation cake!

05:57.482 --> 05:58.483
[ trolls gasp ]

05:58.483 --> 06:03.530
[ cheering ]

06:03.530 --> 06:09.286
[ scream ]

06:11.538 --> 06:13.290
‐ Branch? Are you okay?

06:13.707 --> 06:14.875
‐ No, I'm not.

06:15.208 --> 06:16.793
Look, I know you guys wanna help,

06:16.793 --> 06:19.004
but you haven't passed a single test.

06:19.921 --> 06:21.631
And without a Bunker Nanny...

06:22.507 --> 06:25.802
I'll have to spend
a lot less time in TrollsTopia...

06:28.972 --> 06:31.266
‐ Guys, we have
to pull through for Branch.

06:31.558 --> 06:35.395
So, what do you say we really focus
and show him what we're capable of?

06:36.855 --> 06:38.732
♪ There's nothing you can't do ♪

06:39.316 --> 06:41.526
♪ If you put your mind to it, to it ♪

06:41.526 --> 06:43.695
♪ Don't matter if you planned to ♪

06:43.695 --> 06:46.239
♪ If you believe you can do it, do it ♪

06:46.448 --> 06:47.991
♪ Just work like you want it ♪

06:47.991 --> 06:49.075
♪ Already on it ♪

06:49.075 --> 06:51.161
♪ Never let up or for a moment ♪

06:51.161 --> 06:52.704
♪ All sweating together ♪

06:52.704 --> 06:55.915
♪ Tryna be better
Better, better, better ♪

06:56.249 --> 06:58.543
♪ Lemme see you work
Lemme see you struggle ♪

06:58.543 --> 07:01.129
♪ When you come in first
It was worth all the trouble ♪

07:01.129 --> 07:03.548
♪ Show me what you're worth
Lemme see you prove it ♪

07:03.548 --> 07:04.382
♪ Do it ♪

07:04.382 --> 07:07.302
♪ Gonna give it our all
Gonna give it our all ♪

07:07.761 --> 07:09.888
♪ We won't quit, no, we're given it ♪

07:09.888 --> 07:12.140
♪ Our all, gonna give it our all ♪

07:12.557 --> 07:15.060
♪ Pass the test
Prove that we're the best ♪

07:15.060 --> 07:19.981
♪ If we don't ever stop
We will rise to the top ♪

07:19.981 --> 07:21.983
♪ Gonna give it our all ♪

07:21.983 --> 07:23.735
♪ Bunker down, nose to the ground ♪

07:23.735 --> 07:25.820
♪ Gonna give it our all ♪♪

07:26.655 --> 07:27.489
‐ And...

07:27.656 --> 07:28.782
you've all failed!

07:29.240 --> 07:30.158
‐ What?
‐ What?

07:30.450 --> 07:33.787
‐ Failed? Then what was
all that smilin' and noddin'?

07:33.787 --> 07:36.122
‐ Well, that was
because you were improving...

07:36.122 --> 07:38.041
but, ultimately, yeah, still failed.

07:38.041 --> 07:41.711
‐ Dubstep, you said I got 100%
on dirt maintenance!

07:41.711 --> 07:44.923
‐ Well, to pass you need 149%.

07:45.340 --> 07:47.967
‐ But that's not how math works, yo!

07:48.301 --> 07:52.639
‐ Branch, isn't there a tiny chance
your standards are too high?

07:52.889 --> 07:57.268
And isn't there also a tiny chance
it's because, deep down...

07:57.477 --> 07:59.437
you don't want anyone to pass your test?

07:59.771 --> 08:00.647
[ chuckle ]

08:00.980 --> 08:02.273
‐ Sorry, you lost me.

08:02.273 --> 08:04.859
Why would I make a test
that no one can pass?

08:05.026 --> 08:09.406
‐ 'Cuz you're scared to trust someone else
with your bunker, sugar.

08:09.698 --> 08:12.742
‐ Mm‐hm.
‐ Yeah, Dubstep, like Poppy said...

08:13.034 --> 08:16.162
we know you got mad feelings
for this place, aight?

08:16.162 --> 08:17.080
‐ Yes.
‐ Mm‐hm...

08:17.080 --> 08:18.415
‐ Mad feelings.

08:19.207 --> 08:20.041
‐ What?

08:20.291 --> 08:22.419
Pfft, no, that's‐‐ that's absurd.

08:22.585 --> 08:24.212
Of course the test can be passed.

08:24.212 --> 08:25.213
In fact...

08:25.422 --> 08:26.506
I'll prove it!

08:26.840 --> 08:29.134
Activate "The Final Exam."

08:29.634 --> 08:31.428
BUNKER SYSTEM:
<i>Final Exam engaged.</i>

08:31.428 --> 08:33.972
<i>Total bunker failure in 90 seconds...</i>

08:33.972 --> 08:34.973
[ scream ]

08:34.973 --> 08:37.350
‐ Oh... "Total bunker failure," eh?

08:37.767 --> 08:39.519
Oof, that sounds horrific.

08:40.061 --> 08:41.771
‐ Branch! What are you waiting for?

08:41.771 --> 08:42.647
‐ Shh, shh, shh!

08:48.236 --> 08:49.070
Go.

08:50.238 --> 08:51.072
‐ Huh?
‐ Huh?

08:58.705 --> 09:00.415
‐ Wow!
‐ Wow!

09:04.044 --> 09:07.797
BUNKER SYSTEM:
<i>Well done, Branch, you are scoring 1000%.</i>

09:08.214 --> 09:09.924
‐ Ha‐ha! Thanks, Bunker!

09:10.425 --> 09:13.053
‐ But that's not how math works, yo!

09:22.896 --> 09:24.606
‐ Ooh!
‐ Ooh!

09:28.485 --> 09:31.112
‐ See? Passed with flying colors.

09:32.989 --> 09:33.823
Ah!

09:34.449 --> 09:36.826
Now, I believe I deserve an apology.

09:37.327 --> 09:39.829
BUNKER SYSTEM:
<i>Total bunker failure imminent...</i>

09:39.829 --> 09:41.289
‐ Wait, what?

09:41.915 --> 09:44.167
[ groaning ]

09:44.375 --> 09:45.251
‐ Oh, no, I...

09:45.794 --> 09:47.545
forgot to jiggle the handle.

09:52.926 --> 09:54.052
[ scream ]

09:55.470 --> 09:56.888
[ Synth groans ]

09:57.055 --> 09:59.474
‐ Just a reminder: I've got water powers.

10:00.183 --> 10:03.770
Also, a heads up:
I can't hold it back much longer!

10:04.104 --> 10:05.605
‐ Branch, what do we do?

10:05.605 --> 10:07.524
‐ I‐‐ I‐‐ I don't know!

10:07.774 --> 10:12.737
‐ I'll tell you what we do:
we get busy nannyin'!

10:19.828 --> 10:20.662
‐ Ha!

10:38.263 --> 10:39.848
BRANCH:
You‐‐ you guys...

10:41.349 --> 10:42.183
thank you.

10:42.517 --> 10:43.726
You saved the bunker...

10:44.644 --> 10:45.770
‐ No problem, Branch.

10:46.104 --> 10:47.105
We're here to help.

10:47.814 --> 10:50.066
‐ Yeah... I know you are, but...

10:50.775 --> 10:53.278
I think I wasn't letting you
'cuz you were right...

10:53.486 --> 10:56.489
I am scared to let someone else
take care of my bunker.

10:57.448 --> 10:58.324
I'm sorry.

10:58.992 --> 11:00.160
‐ Aw!
‐ Aw!

11:00.910 --> 11:03.913
‐ But now I see
I shouldn't have been looking

11:03.913 --> 11:06.457
for someone to care for my bunker...

11:06.583 --> 11:09.085
I should've been looking for someones.

11:09.836 --> 11:10.670
[ gasp ]

11:11.212 --> 11:13.715
‐ Wait, Branch, do you mean...?

11:13.715 --> 11:17.177
‐ Yes, it's so obvious!
With all four of you,

11:17.177 --> 11:20.054
working together as a team
of Bunker Nannies...

11:20.054 --> 11:23.349
I'd never need to worry
about the bunker ever again!

11:23.349 --> 11:27.270
[ cheering ]

11:28.897 --> 11:30.106
‐ Wait...

11:30.315 --> 11:34.152
Are you sayin' it takes four of us
to replace one of you?

11:35.612 --> 11:38.239
‐ Oh‐‐ I‐‐ um...

11:42.744 --> 11:43.745
[ trolls murmur ]

11:43.745 --> 11:45.747
POPPY:
Thank you for gathering, Trolls.

11:45.747 --> 11:49.209
You are never gonna guess
the big surprise we have for you!

11:50.418 --> 11:52.253
‐ Is it that massive pile of dominoes?

11:54.797 --> 11:55.715
[ scream ]

11:56.799 --> 11:57.634
‐ Yes.

11:57.634 --> 11:58.718
[ trolls murmur ]

11:58.718 --> 12:02.472
‐ Woo‐hoo! Where'd we get
such an intense pile of dominoes anyway?

12:02.722 --> 12:06.059
‐ Well, last night
at the Funtime Factory, there was a...

12:06.601 --> 12:07.852
chain reaction...

12:10.438 --> 12:11.564
[ trolls cheering ]

12:26.621 --> 12:32.043
‐ So, long story hilarious,
we now have 100 million dominoes!

12:32.252 --> 12:35.630
And you can't imagine the fun plan
we have in store for them!

12:36.547 --> 12:39.884
‐ Is it to build an elaborate domino chain
like the one on that table?

12:44.347 --> 12:45.181
‐ Yes!

12:45.181 --> 12:46.391
‐ Ooh!
‐ Ooh!

12:46.391 --> 12:47.892
‐ I don't mean to brag,

12:47.892 --> 12:51.354
but I've built a lot
of domino lines in my day.

12:51.354 --> 12:53.982
And I'm telling ya, if we worked together,

12:54.274 --> 12:58.569
we could construct the kind of chain
that every dominophile dreams about!

12:58.945 --> 13:00.571
But on an epic scale...

13:00.780 --> 13:02.991
crossing through all of TrollsTopia...

13:03.283 --> 13:05.743
culminating at the stadium
for a grand finale

13:05.743 --> 13:08.371
the likes of which Trollkind
has never witnessed!

13:08.663 --> 13:11.416
‐ Wow! I've never seen...
‐ Yeah!

13:13.167 --> 13:15.169
‐ And if that doesn't convince you,

13:15.378 --> 13:18.047
then perhaps this song
and dance number will...

13:21.009 --> 13:23.469
♪ Well ♪♪

13:23.469 --> 13:24.304
R:
Nope!

13:24.804 --> 13:28.599
Not necessary, Branch,
we love the dominoes idea!

13:28.599 --> 13:30.351
‐ You completely sold us!

13:30.685 --> 13:32.562
‐ Oh... okay...

13:33.062 --> 13:36.107
it's just I worked
really hard on this song, but...

13:38.192 --> 13:41.070
‐ Uh, I‐‐ I mean... boo!

13:41.070 --> 13:43.197
You have not convinced us!

13:43.364 --> 13:45.533
‐ We are squarely on the fence!

13:45.992 --> 13:46.826
[ gasp ]

13:46.826 --> 13:48.327
♪ Well... ♪

13:48.327 --> 13:50.246
♪ Everybody, everybody gather round ♪

13:50.246 --> 13:52.248
♪ I got an idea
That's gonna rock the town ♪

13:52.248 --> 13:54.167
♪ Let's take every single last domino ♪

13:54.167 --> 13:56.169
♪ And line them up
As far as they can go! ♪

13:56.169 --> 13:58.004
♪ Cause the longer the chain ♪

13:58.004 --> 13:59.881
♪ The greater the cascade ♪

13:59.881 --> 14:01.674
♪ Nothing can compare, no ♪

14:01.674 --> 14:03.760
♪ I promise you're all gonna be amazed ♪

14:03.760 --> 14:06.345
♪ Magic right before your eyes ♪

14:06.345 --> 14:07.555
♪ So mesmerizing ♪

14:07.555 --> 14:10.099
♪ Everyone gets butterflies ♪

14:10.099 --> 14:11.350
♪ It's unsurprising ♪

14:11.350 --> 14:12.310
♪ Who? ♪

14:12.310 --> 14:13.186
♪ You! ♪

14:13.186 --> 14:15.438
♪ Everybody's gonna like
What we do cause... ♪

14:15.438 --> 14:17.190
♪ Dominoes are calling ♪

14:17.190 --> 14:19.942
♪ Line 'em up
Then watch 'em fallin' down! ♪♪

14:21.402 --> 14:22.320
‐ Oh!
‐ Oh!

14:27.283 --> 14:28.367
‐ Hey, Laguna!
‐ Ah!

14:29.243 --> 14:30.787
‐ We need a hand with the finale.

14:30.787 --> 14:33.414
Branch has described it
as "brutally intricate."

14:33.414 --> 14:34.248
[ chuckle ]

14:34.248 --> 14:36.542
‐ He's so pumped... Wanna come help?

14:36.751 --> 14:39.754
‐ Do I? Poppy, I adore dominoes...

14:40.004 --> 14:43.591
The precision, the careful dance
of cause and effect...

14:43.591 --> 14:45.802
There are few past times I love more!

14:46.928 --> 14:48.679
But, no, absolutely not.

14:50.306 --> 14:53.184
‐ Wha‐‐? Wait, you're not gonna be part
of the build at all?

14:53.184 --> 14:54.811
‐ Correct. You see,

14:54.811 --> 14:58.981
I've had an unfortunate history
of prematurely knocking over domino lines

14:58.981 --> 15:00.733
and ruining them for everyone.

15:01.025 --> 15:02.068
I call it my...

15:02.568 --> 15:03.986
Domin‐Uh‐Oh's.

15:05.655 --> 15:09.659
‐ Wow... So unfortunate
and yet so adorably named.

15:10.243 --> 15:13.454
I'm sorry, Laguna,
but I'm sure it's just a matter

15:13.454 --> 15:14.831
of being a bit more careful.

15:14.831 --> 15:17.959
‐ Ah, but that's where you'd be utterly,
utterly wrong.

15:18.376 --> 15:21.129
Being careful makes things far worse!

15:21.462 --> 15:25.508
<i>You see, there are just so many places</i>
<i>to bump domino tracks...</i>

15:25.716 --> 15:29.137
<i>I start to fixate on all</i>
<i>the different things that could go wrong.</i>

15:29.387 --> 15:32.765
<i>Soon, I can't relax at all,</i>
<i>which leads to...</i>

15:33.391 --> 15:35.601
<i>infuriatingly simple mistakes.</i>

